BUILD YOUR OFFER
-----------------------
- make an irresistible offer
- make an offer so good people would feel stupid to say no

1. identify dream outcome
	- lose 20lbs in 6 weeks
	- big dream outcome - lose 20lbs
	- with a cecreased time delay - 6 weeks
	- dont sell the plane flight, sell the vacation

2. list problems
	- list people struggles and limiting beliefs
	- think what happens immediately before and after someone uses your
	  product
	- what's the next thing they need help with
	- think about it in insane detail
	- e.g.
		- buy healthy food is hard, confusing, and I won't like it
		- buying healty food will take too much time
		- buying healthy food is expensive
		- i will not be able to cook healthy food forever. my family's
		  needs will get in my way. if i travel i won't know what to
get
		- cooking healthy food is hard and confusiong. i wont like it
		  and i will such at it
		- will take too much time
		- is expensive, it's not worth it
		- not able to buy helahty food forever. my family in my way.
		  if i travel...

	1. dream outcome: this will not be financially worth it
	2. likelihood: this wont work for me specifically. can't stick with
it, external factors
	3. effort sacrifice: too hard, confusing, wont like it, suck at it
	4. time: too much time, too busy, take long to work, not convenient
	
	- the more problem you can think, the more problem you can solve
	- list all core thinks people has to do, and think of all reasons they
	  will not be able to do it

3. solution list
	1. transform problems into solutions
	2. name those solutions
	- pick each problem and add "how to" at the beginning to reverse the
	  problem into solution
	- you must solve every problem, even 1 problem is enough to kill the
	  sale

	- e.g.
		- buying healthy food is hard, confusing, i wont like it...
		- ->how to make buying healhty food easy and enjoyable
	- most problem repeats, it's ok

	- overdeliver like crazy
	- you want them ro perceive tremendous value
	- everyone buys bargains

	- continuum between ease of fulfillment and ease of sales
	- find the sweet spot

